## Connecting to Redshift and reading in Sun King sales data

con=psycopg2.connect(dbname='dev',
                     host='glp-payg-database.cedhxs8itccy.us-west-2.redshift.amazonaws.com',
                     port='5439',user='glppayg',password='EasyBuy2016')

sql1 = """
    SELECT 
           accounts.angaza_id,
           accounts.area_derived as area,
           accounts.region,
           accounts.country,
           COALESCE(
               NULLIF(accounts.unit_location_latitudelongitude,''),
               NULLIF(accounts.registration_location_latitudelongitude,'')
               ) AS latlong, -- get coordinates from whatever column has it
           split_part(latlong,',', 1)::DECIMAL(6,4)  AS "unit_lat",
           split_part(latlong,',', 2)::DECIMAL(7,4)  AS "unit_long"           

      FROM easybuy.accounts_final_pdt AS accounts
     WHERE split_part(latlong,',',2) <> '' -- check for valid gps  
       AND accounts.registration_date_utc::DATETIME       >    '2023-01-01' 
       AND accounts.country                               =    'Kenya'
       -- AND product_group                                  LIKE 'SHS%'
       -- AND region = 'Nyanza' -- Kenya
       -- AND area in ('Akoko') -- Nigeria
     LIMIT 1e7
     """

# TODO: add filter for customers who have not been visited by ACLE recently
#      -- FROM kazi_prod.fse_base_location as base
     
# --        ON base.angaza_id = accounts.responsible_user_angaza_id
# shs 400 600
# df_acc: one row per account, columns include plan length, country, product name
df_base = pd.read_sql(sql1, con)
df_base.set_index('angaza_id', inplace=True)
print("\n\n\n# of accounts: ", df_base.shape[0], "\n\n\n")
df_base.head(2)

In [62]:
def plot_examples(cms):
    """
    helper function to plot two colormaps
    """
    np.random.seed(19680801)
    data = np.random.randn(30, 30)

    fig, axs = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(6, 3), constrained_layout=True)
    for [ax, cmap] in zip(axs, cms):
        psm = ax.pcolormesh(data, cmap=cmap, rasterized=True, vmin=-4, vmax=4)
        fig.colorbar(psm, ax=ax)
    plt.show()

plot_examples([viridis, newcmp])
